tion of hostilities and wondered if all those worldwide who had provided support and assistance to kosovar refugees could give the same attention to the refugees in the congo afghanistan and sudan linda tripp incidentedit see also lewinsky scandal in march  bacon released details of employee linda tripps personnel file to a reporter disclosing that tripp had omitted on her employment application an incident that occurred when she was arrested for theft when she was  years old tripp a defense department employee had been a friend of monica lewinsky who had herself worked as an assistant in bacons office in  and  having been hired on the recommendation of the white house bacon was criticized for violating privacy laws and harming tripps reputation in response to a defense department inspector generals report in  that concluded that bacon had not followed authorized procedures william cohen published a letter that had been sent to bacon in which bacons actions were called hasty and illconceived bacon issued a statement that the information he released was driven by a desire to be responsive to an urgent media inquiry and that the inspector generals twoyear investigation did not find any connection to the white house in a  settlement following a lawsuit which claimed that the revelations violated the privacy act of  tripp received a payment of  retroactive promotion and salary increases for the years  to  and the right to reapply for government employment refugees internationaledit main article refugees international bacon recognized that becoming a refugee was a matter of circumstance that could affect anyone noting that his own blueblooded wasp ancestors were refugees themselves who came over from england in  fleeing debts for all i know after leaving his government post in  bacon became president of refugees international which compels the worlds leaders to assist the millions worldwide who have fled their homes due to violence or persecution the organization regularly assists and provides guidance to government and un agencies including peacekeeping bodies on ways to serve the needs of refugees bacon focused much of his work on advocating for additional protection and assistance to displaced people from sudans darfur region and iraq he was also active in drawing international attention to displaced people in afghanistan burma the democratic republic of congo colombia and thailand during bacons tenure as president of refugees international the organization doubled in size in the weeks before the start of the  invasion of iraq bacon suggested such methods as selection of bombing targets outside of densely populated areas as a means to reduce the number of refugees in september  bacon encouraged french participation in the peacekeeping forces in iraq based on that nations prior experience in such circumstances emphasizing that the us cannot afford to win the military battle and lose the humanitarian campaign in iraq bacon advocated for increased numbers of iraqi refugees to be allowed to enter the united states and for greater american financial assistance to refugees from violence in iraq with funding from the state department rising from  million in  to  in  five days before his death august  refugees international announced that bacon had endowed a new program to focus on people displaced by climate change personal lifeedit bacon wrote an essay about health care reform from his own perspective as a cancer patient a matter of life and death for him that was published in the washington post  days before his death he offered prevention and online efficiencies among his recommendations with his own example of melanoma that could have been treatable if caught earlier given a family history of the condition he described his difficulties in getting approval for payment of radiation therapy for cancer that had spread to his brain which his insurer had deemed not medically necessary and expressed his frustration with the amount of time he and his physician had to spend in dealing with paperwork he served as chairman of the folger shakespeare library and was a member of the council on foreign relations and the international institute for strategic studies deathedit a resident of washington dc bacon died at age  of complications related to melanoma at his second home on block island rhode island he was survived by his two daughters and his wife of  years the former darcy wheeler referencesedit  a b c d e f g h i martin douglas k h bacon an advocate for refugees is dead at  the new york times august   accessed august    staff ken bacon  receives john phillips award archived  at the wayback machine philips exeter academy press release october   accessed august    a b c d e stephen miller  miller stephen he helped worlds refugees the wall street journal august    a b c d e schudel matt pentagon spokesman became an advocate for refugees the washington post august    becker elizabeth  officials rebuked for tripp disclosures the new york times may   accessed august    via associated press defense dept settles with linda tripp usa today november   accessed august    seeley tina kenneth bacon president of refugees international dies at  bloomberg news august    seeley tina obituary associated press august    bacon kenneth h a cancer patients perspective the washington post july   accessed august   external linksedit wikimedia commons has media related to kenneth bacon associated press obituary the washington post american forces press service obituary united states department of defense refugees international tribute page authority control worldcat identities viaf  retrieved from httpsenwikipediaorgwindexphptitlekennethbaconoldid categories american columnistsamerican public relations peopleamherst college alumnideaths from cancer in rhode islandclinton administration personnelcolumbia business school alumnicolumbia university graduate school of journalism alumnideaths from melanomaamerican nonprofit execu